ArrayBuffers
------------
These are arrays of 8 bit bytes

Created with new ArrayBuffer(bytelength)

has .byteLength property


TYPED ARRAYS
------------
These are arrays of numeric types 
such as 
Int8Array()
Uint8Array()
UintClampedArray()  -will clamp values to 0-255
Int32Array()
Uint16Array()
Float64Array()

These are placed 'over' ArrayBuffers which holds the values and tell us how to "read" the byte arrays

